SHIRE, ENGLAND":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Deighton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Deighton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice was born in 1325, in Deighton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She married John de Deighton about 1348, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1401, in her hometown, at the age of 76."},"et":{"1325–1401":"1325–1401","1325–1420":"1325–1420","1348–Male":"1348–Surnud","1350–1381":"1350–1381","1348":"1348","1325":"1325","1401":"1401","1420":"1420","about 1348":"umbes 1348","1350":"1350","1381":"1381","Deighton, Yorkshire, England":"Deighton, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","YORKSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Deighton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Deighton, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1325–1401":"1325–1401","1325–1420":"1325–1420","1348–Male":"1348–Kuollut","1350–1381":"1350–1381","1348":"1348","1325":"1325","1401":"1401","1420":"1420","about 1348":"noin 1348","1350":"1350","1381":"1381","Deighton, Yorkshire, England":"Deighton, Yorkshire, En